Arthur Hunnicutt https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthur_Hunnicutt 0 Arthur Lee Hunnicutt (February 17, 1910 – September 26, 1979) was an American actor known for his portrayal of wise, grizzled, and old rural characters. He received an Academy Award nomination for Best Supporting Actor for his performance in The Big Sky (1952).
